{{unreferenced|date=February 2009}} {{korean name|[[Choi (Korean name)|Choe]]}} {{Infobox Korean name| hangul=최준| hanja=崔浚| rr=Choe Jun| mr=Ch'oe Chun| }}
'''Choe Jun''' (1884&ndash;1970) was a businessman and philanthropist in early 20th-century [[Korea]]. He was born in [[Gyeongju]], in present-day [[South Korea]]. His family, known as the "Choe Bujatjip," had been known since the 17th century for their wealth and public-spiritedness. After the liberation of Korea in 1945, he gave much of his fortune to the [[Yeungnam University]] Foundation. He spent his later years in Suji, [[Yongin]] ([[Gyeonggi]] province).
